        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10032",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=willie",
                        "name": "willie",
                        "displayName": "Willie Alberty",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue necessitates a change to the public API. Specific details to follow...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=willie",
                        "name": "willie",
                        "displayName": "Willie Alberty",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-16T23:43:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-16T23:43:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10043",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=willie",
                        "name": "willie",
                        "displayName": "Willie Alberty",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Done. This issue caused a backwards-incompatible API change. To repair your code, you will need to perform the following global search-and-replace operations:\n\n{noformat} \nZend_Pdf_Const::PAGESIZE_     ->  Zend_Pdf_Page::SIZE_\nZend_Pdf_Const::SHAPEDRAW_    ->  Zend_Pdf_Page::SHAPEDRAW_\nZend_Pdf_Const::FILLMETHOD_   ->  Zend_Pdf_Page::FILLMETHOD_\nZend_Pdf_Const::LINEDASHING_  ->  Zend_Pdf_Page::LINEDASHING_\nZend_Pdf_Const::PDF_          ->  Zend_Pdf::PDF_\nZend_Pdf_Const::pdfDate()     ->  Zend_Pdf::pdfDate()\n{noformat} \n\nIn addition, font object creation has been revamped. Font objects are now instantiated via a factory methods. You will also need to perform the following global search-and-replace operation:\n\n{noformat} \nnew Zend_Pdf_Font_Standard(Zend_Pdf_Const::FONT_  ->\n  Zend_Pdf_Font::fontWithName(Zend_Pdf_Font::FONT_\n{noformat} \n\nFinally, the old static arrays {{$pageSizeAliases}} and {{$standardFonts}} have been completely removed. There are no replacements.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=willie",
                        "name": "willie",
                        "displayName": "Willie Alberty",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-17T14:33:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-17T14:33:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10048",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=willie",
                        "name": "willie",
                        "displayName": "Willie Alberty",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "On Jun 17, 2006, at 4:04 PM, andi@zend.com wrote:\n\nI have one piece of feedback though. The constants (not sure if you are responsible for naming them or not) don't use underscores to separate words. I think it'd be much nicer to do so. I know we have it in the PHP coding standards, but not sure if we wrote it in the ZFW coding standards (if not we should).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=willie",
                        "name": "willie",
                        "displayName": "Willie Alberty",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-17T17:26:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-17T17:26:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10049",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=willie",
                        "name": "willie",
                        "displayName": "Willie Alberty",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Implemented Andi's request. All constants in Zend_Pdf now have underscores between words.\n\n{panel:title=NOTE: Due to this change, ignore the instructions above and use these instead.|titleBGColor=#F7D6C1|bgColor=#FFFFCE}\nTo repair your code, you will need to perform the following global search-and-replace operations:\n\n{noformat}\nZend_Pdf_Const::PAGESIZE_                 -> Zend_Pdf_Page::SIZE_\nZend_Pdf_Const::SHAPEDRAW_FILLNSTROKE     -> Zend_Pdf_Page::SHAPE_DRAW_FILL_AND_STROKE\nZend_Pdf_Const::SHAPEDRAW_                -> Zend_Pdf_Page::SHAPE_DRAW_\nZend_Pdf_Const::FILLMETHOD_NONZEROWINDING -> Zend_Pdf_Page::FILL_METHOD_NON_ZERO_WINDING\nZend_Pdf_Const::FILLMETHOD_EVENODD        -> Zend_Pdf_Page::FILL_METHOD_EVEN_ODD\nZend_Pdf_Const::LINEDASHING_              -> Zend_Pdf_Page::LINE_DASHING_\nZend_Pdf_Const::PDF_                      -> Zend_Pdf::PDF_\nZend_Pdf_Const::pdfDate()                 -> Zend_Pdf::pdfDate()\n{noformat}\n\nIn addition, font object creation has been revamped. Font objects are now instantiated via a factory methods. You will also need to perform the following global search-and-replace operations:\n\n{noformat}\nnew Zend_Pdf_Font_Standard(Zend_Pdf_Const::FONT_  ->\n  Zend_Pdf_Font::fontWithName(Zend_Pdf_Font::FONT_\n\n_BOLDITALIC  ->  _BOLD_ITALIC\n{noformat}\n\nFinally, the old static arrays $pageSizeAliases and $standardFonts have been completely removed. There are no replacements.\n{panel}\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=willie",
                        "name": "willie",
                        "displayName": "Willie Alberty",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-17T19:11:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-17T19:11:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10051",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=willie",
                        "name": "willie",
                        "displayName": "Willie Alberty",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Updated the coding standards document as well: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFDEV\/Zend+Framework+PHP+Coding+Standard",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=willie",
                        "name": "willie",
                        "displayName": "Willie Alberty",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-17T19:23:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-17T19:23:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21918",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This change was made eons ago (in Zend Framework time) but the file Zend\/Pdf\/Const.php still exists.  At this point it is safe to remove it entirely.",
